body:
@peng-yongsheng reported this conflict. As they used to extend the same core service, when both of them are active, which could happen, they can't work together.

But, from the design perspective, I notice, ignore plugin actually is just a sampling service. It used `ContextManagerExtendService` extension, just because only sampling service API doesn't provide the operation name.

In this PR, I changed the sampling service API, and move `TraceIgnoreExtendService` to extend it. So conflict goes away.

Since the beginning of SkyWalking, we have concerns of using tags as trace query conditions, but this requirement keeps showing up. In this pull request, I implement this feature in ElasticSearch 6/7 and H2/MySQL/TiDB storages. InfluxDB will be implemented by @dmsolr later.

The latest trace query GraphQL, https://github.com/apache/skywalking-query-protocol/blob/master/trace.graphqls#L50

UI and CLI could use multiple tags(`key=value`) to filter the traces with all other conditions. The example of new query looks like this
```graphql
{
  queryBasicTraces(condition : {
    traceState: ALL,
    queryOrder: BY_START_TIME,
    queryDuration : {
      step:MINUTE, start: "2020-08-08 2200", end: "2020-08-08 2300"
    },
    paging: {
      pageNum: 0,
      pageSize: 50,
      needTotal: false
    },
    # Duplicate keys are allowed, because one segment includes multiple spans, those spans could have different tag values
    tags: [{
      key: "status_code"
      value: "404"
    },{
      key: "status_code"
      value: "200"
    }]
  }
  ) {
    total,
    traces {
      segmentId,
      endpointNames,
      duration,
      traceIds
    }
  }
}
```
